Historical simulations cover the mid-1850s to at least 2005 (
 Mieville et al. 2010; 
 Schultz et al. 2008; 
 van der Werf et al. 2006). These simulations permit the evaluation of model performance against present and observed climate change. Additionally, historical simulations allow for the analysis of human impacts on past climate and also provide initial conditions for future scenarios of greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions and anthropogenic activities described by the RCP scenarios (
 Taylor et al. 2012).
